27/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu said Thursday (26 May) that fighting corruption should be the country's priority. 
He added that for this fight to be efficient, "justice has to be freed from political cuffs". 
He urged all relevant authorities to meet their obligations to Romania's 22 million citizens and break any ties to suspicious groups. 
He added that only through eliminating corruption would the dignity of Romania be restored. 
(Rompres - 26/05/05)
